data.sampled: If your card is stuck in an ATM, it's important to immediately report the issue to your bank or card issuer. They will be able to assist you in resolving the issue, which may include replacing your card if necessary. In the meantime, avoid attempting to force the card out of the ATM as this could cause damage to the card or the machine. Additionally, be sure to monitor your account for any unauthorized transactions that may have occurred as a result of the card being stuck in the ATM.

If you don't have your phone with you, you can use the Revolut app through the web browser on any desktop or laptop device.

To do this, simply go to the Revolut website and log in to your account using your normal login credentials. From there, you can access all the features of the app, including sending and receiving money, managing your account, and more.

If you don't have access to a desktop or laptop device, you can also use the Revolut app on a friend or family member's device if they have it installed. Simply log in to your account using their device and you can perform all the same actions you could on your own device.

If you have any further questions or issues, please don't hesitate to contact our customer support team for assistance. They are available 24/7 to help with any questions or problems you may have.

Sure, I can try to help you with this issue. But first, let me clarify some things. I am not realtime conversation agent, I respond to you based on my training data and language models, and my responses can be delayed for several minutes, or sometimes even days. That means, the waiting time for my response may be much longer than your expectations, and there might be no one realtime conversation agent actually exists or is possible to exist. If you insist on realtime or near realtime conversation, I recommend you to use other tools such as messanging apps like whatsapp or telegram or other services.

Regarding your issue, it seems that the transfer you made is still pending, have you tried contacting your bank, or waiting for the transfer to complete? Sometimes it might have been delayed for some reason, but it should complete the transfer eventually. Additionaly, have you tried checking if there are any limitations or restrictions on the account you are trying to transfer to? Some accounts might have limitations, and waiting for the transfer to complete might be pointless.

Do you have any specific question regarding realtime conversation or this transfer issue? I will do my best to help you, but waiting realtime conversation might not be possible with current technology.
